obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39073)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39073&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Andhra Pradesh and Madras`
  line `(Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1959.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st April, 1960, vide Notification No. S.O. 2863, dated 29th December, 1959, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39074)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39074&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date appointed under sub-section (2) of section 1 for the coming`
  line `into force of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "assembly constituency", "council constituency" and "parliamentary constituency" have the`
  line `same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(c) "law" includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `or Madras;`
  line
  line `(d) "notified order" means an order published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "sitting member", in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that House;`
  line
  line `(f) "transferred territories" means—`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the State of Andhra Pradesh, the territories specified in the Second Schedule`
  line `and transferred from that State to Madras; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to the State of Madras, the territories specified in the First Schedule and`
  line `transferred from that State to Andhra Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(g) "treasury" includes a sub-treasury;`
  line
  line `(h) any reference to a district, taluk, firka, village or other territorial division of a State shall be`
  line `construed as a reference to the area comprised within that territorial division on the 1st day of July,`
  line 1957.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39075)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer of territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39075&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, there shall be added—`
  line
  line `(a) to the State of Andhra Pradesh, the territories specified in the First Schedule which shall`
  line `thereupon cease to form part of the State of Madras; and`
  line
  line `(b) to the State of Madras, the territories specified in the Second Schedule which shall thereupon`
  line `cease to form part of the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39076)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Changes of territorial divisions in Andhra Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39076&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The territories specified in Part I of`
  line `the First Schedule shall be included in, and form part of, Chittoor district; and the said territories, together`
  line `with the territories comprised in the villages of Puttur taluk specified in the Third Schedule and the`
  line `territories which immediately before the appointed day were comprised in Kanakammachatram and`
  line `Tiruttani firkas of Tiruttani taluk but are not transferred by virtue of section 3 of the State of Madras, shall`
  line `form a taluk to be known as Sathyavedu taluk in Chittoor district.`
  line
  line `(2) The territories which immediately before the appointed day were comprised in Palliputtu and`
  line `Erumbi firkas of Tiruttani taluk but are not transferred by virtue of section 3 to the State of Madras shall`
  line `be included in, and form part of, Puttur taluk.`
  line
  line `(3) The territories which immediately before the appointed day were comprised in Melpadi firka of`
  line `Chittoor taluk but are not transferred by virtue of section 3 to the State of Madras shall be included in, and`
  line `form part of, Chittoor firka of Chittoor taluk.`
  line
  line `(4) The territories specified in Part II of the First Schedule shall be included in, and form part of,`
  line `Kuppam West firka of Palmaner taluk in Chittoor district.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39077)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Changes of territorial divisions in Madras.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39077&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The territories which immediately before the`
  line `appointed day were comprised in Sathyavedu firka of Ponneri taluk and Uttukkottai firka of Tiruvallur`
  line `taluk but are not transferred by virtue of section 3 to the State of Andhra Pradesh shall be included in, and`
  line `form part of, Gummidipundi firka of Ponneri taluk.`
  line
  line `(2) The territories specified in Parts I and II of the Second Schedule shall be included in and form a`
  line `separate taluk to be known as Tiruttani taluk of Chingleput district; and in that taluk, the territories`
  line `specified in Part II of that Schedule shall form a separate firka to be known as Kanakammachatram firka.`
  line
  line `(3) The territories specified in Parts III, IV, V, VI, VII and VIII of the Second Schedule shall`
  line `respectively be included in, and form part of,—`
  line
  line `(a) Mappedu firka of Tiruvallur taluk of Chingleput district,`
  line
  line `(b) Paranji firka of Arkonam taluk of North Arcot district,`
  line
  line `(c) Arkonam firka of Arkonam taluk of North Arcot district,`
  line
  line `(d) Ranipet firka of Walajapet taluk of North Arcot district,`
  line
  line `(e) Gudiyattam East Firka of Gudiyattam taluk of North Arcot district, and`
  line
  line `(f) Vaniyambadi firka of Tiruppattur taluk of North Arcot district.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39078)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39078&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the First`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, under the heading "I. THE STATES",—`
  line
  line `(a) for the entry against "1. Andhra Pradesh", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"The territories specified in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Andhra State Act, 1953,`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956, and the First Schedule to the`
  line `Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of Boundaries) Act, 1959, but excluding the territories`
  line `specified in the Second Schedule to the last mentioned Act,"; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the entry against "7. Madras",—`
  line
  line `(i) after the words and figures "section 4 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956", the words,`
  line `brackets and figures "and the Second Schedule to the Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of`
  line `Boundaries) Act, 1959," shall be inserted; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the words, brackets, letters and figures "and the territories specified in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5, section 6 and clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 7 of the States`
  line `Reorganisation Act, 1956", the following shall be substituted, namely:—`
  line
  line `"the territories specified in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 5, section 6 and`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 7 of the States Reorganisation Act, 1956 and the`
  line `territories specified in the First Schedule to the Andhra Pradesh and Madras (Alteration of`
  line `Boundaries) Act, 1959".`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39079)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Saving powers of State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39079&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the foregoing provisions of this Part shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the power of the State Government of Andhra Pradesh or Madras to alter after the`
  line `appointed day the name, extent or boundaries of any district, taluk, firka or village in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39080)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Amendment of Fourth Schedule to the Constitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39080&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `As from the appointed day, in the Fourth`
  line `Schedule to the Constitution, in the second column of the Table,—`
  line
  line `(a) for the figures "17" against Madras, the figures "18" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the figures "220", the figures "221" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39081)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bye-election to fill the additional seat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39081&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the appointed day, a`
  line `bye-election shall be held to fill the additional seat allotted to the State of Madras in the Council of States`
  line `by virtue of section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) The term of office of the member elected to the Council of States in pursuance of this section shall`
  line `expire on the 2nd day of April, 1962.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39082)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Amendment of First Schedule to the Delimitation Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39082&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The First Schedule to the`
  line `Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1956, shall have effect subject to the`
  line `modifications specified in the Fourth Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39083)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provision as to sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39083&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every sitting member of the House of the People representing`
  line `a constituency the extent of which is altered by virtue of section 10 shall be deemed to have been elected`
  line `to the said House by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39084)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Strength of Legislative Assemblies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39084&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh to be filled by persons chosen by direct election shall be reduced from 301 to 300 and`
  line `that in the Legislative Assembly of Madras shall be increased from 205 to 206; and, accordingly, in the`
  line `Second Schedule to the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950), for the figures "301" against`
  line `"Andhra Pradesh", the figures "300" shall be substituted, and for the figures "205" against "Madras", the`
  line `figures 206 shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39085)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Amendment of Second Schedule to Delimitation Order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39085&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Second Schedule to the`
  line `Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 1956, shall have effect subject to the`
  line `modifications specified in the Fifth Schedule to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39086)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Amendment of Delimitation Commission’s Final Order No. 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39086&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Delimitation`
  line `Commission's Final Order No. 19, dated the 4th October, 1954, shall have effect subject to the`
  line `modifications specified in the Sixth Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39087)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Provisions as to certain sitting member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39087&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sitting members of the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Andhra Pradesh representing the Vadamalpet, Vepanjeri, Chittoor and Kuppam`
  line `constituencies shall, notwithstanding the alteration in the extent thereof by the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to have been respectively elected to the said Assembly by the said constituencies as so altered.`
  line
  line `(2) The sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of Madras representing the Gummidipundi,`
  line `Tiruvallur, Arkonam, Sholinghur, Ranipet, Gudiyattam, Vaniyambadi and Uddanapalli constituencies`
  line `shall, notwithstanding the alteration in the extent thereof by the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have`
  line `been respectively elected to the said Assembly by the said constituencies as so altered.`
  line
  line `(3) The sitting members of the Legislative Assembly of Andhra Pradesh representing the Tiruttani`
  line `constituency shall, as from the appointed day, be deemed to have been elected to that Assembly by the`
  line `Sathyavedu constituency in the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(4) The sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of Andhra Pradesh representing the`
  line `Ramakrishnarajupet constituency shall, as from the appointed day, cease to be a member of that`
  line `Assembly and be deemed to have been elected to the Legislative Assembly of Madras from the Tiruttani`
  line `constituency in the State of Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39088)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Extent of Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39088&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any reference in the Delimitation of Council`
  line `Constituencies (Andhra Pradesh) Order, 1957, to the State of Andhra Pradesh or to Chittoor district shall`
  line `be construed as excluding the territories transferred from that State or district, as the case may be, to the`
  line `State of Madras and as including the territories transferred to that State or district, as the case may be,`
  line `from the State of Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Madras) Order, 1951, to the State of`
  line `Madras or to Chingleput, North Arcot or Salem district shall be construed as excluding the territories`
  line `transferred from that State or district, as the case may be, to the State of Andhra Pradesh, and as including`
  line `the territories transferred to that State or district, as the case may be, from the State of Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39089)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Sitting members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39089&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Every sitting member of the Legislative Council of Andhra Pradesh or of`
  line `Madras representing a Council constituency the extent of which is altered by virtue of section 16 shall, as`
  line `from the appointed day, be deemed to have been elected to the said Council by that constituency as so`
  line altered.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39090)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, Andhra Pradesh High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39090&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as hereinafter provided,—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall, as from the appointed day, extend`
  line `to the territories specified in the First Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court at Madras shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in respect of the said`
  line territories.
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court at Madras immediately before the appointed day as`
  line `are certified by the Chief Justice of that High Court, having regard to the place of accrual of the cause of`
  line `action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the High Court`
  line `of Andhra Pradesh shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the High Court of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court at Madras shall have, and the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall not have, jurisdiction to`
  line `entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications`
  line `for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order`
  line `passed by the High Court at Madras before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court at Madras, it appears`
  line `to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court at Madras—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `by virtue of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court at Madras retains jurisdiction by`
  line `virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect, not only as an order of the High Court at Madras, but also as an order`
  line `made by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh, any such`
  line `person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court at`
  line `Madras as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `having regard to the transfer of territories from the State of Madras to the State of Andhra Pradesh, shall`
  line `be recognised as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39091)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Extension of jurisdiction of, and transfer of proceedings to, Madras High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39091&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except`
  line `as hereinafter provided,—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the High Court at Madras shall, as from the appointed day, extend to the`
  line `territories specified in the Second Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall, as from that day, have no jurisdiction in respect of`
  line `the said territories.`
  line
  line `(2) Such proceedings pending in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh immediately before the appointed`
  line `day as are certified by the Chief Justice of the High Court, having regard to the place of accrual of the`
  line `cause of action and other circumstances, to be proceedings which ought to be heard and decided by the`
  line `High Court at Madras shall, as soon as may be after such certification, be transferred to the High Court at`
  line Madras.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2). but save as hereinafter provided,`
  line `the High Court of Andhra Pradesh shall have, and the High Court at Madras shall not have, jurisdiction to`
  line `entertain, hear or dispose of appeals, applications for leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications`
  line `for review and other proceedings, where any such proceedings seek any relief in respect of any order`
  line `passed by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, after such proceedings have been entertained by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh,`
  line `it appears to the Chief Justice of that High Court that they ought to be transferred to the High Court at`
  line `Madras, he shall order that they shall be so transferred, and such proceedings shall thereupon be`
  line `transferred accordingly.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by the High Court of Andhra Pradesh—`
  line
  line `(a) before the appointed day in any proceedings transferred to the High Court at Madras by virtue`
  line `of sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) in any proceedings with respect to which the High Court of Andhra Pradesh retains`
  line `jurisdiction by virtue of sub-section (3),`
  line
  line `shall, for all purposes, have effect, not only as an order of the High Court of Andhra Pradesh, but also as`
  line `an order made by the High Court of Madras.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to any rule made or direction given by the High Court at Madras, any such person who`
  line `immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh as may be specified in this behalf by the Chief Justice of the High Court at Madras having regard`
  line `to the transfer of territories from the State of Andhra Pradesh to the State of Madras, shall be recognised`
  line `as an advocate entitled to practise in the High Court at Madras.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39092)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right to appear or act in any proceedings transferred under section 18 or section 19.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39092&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `person who immediately before the appointed day is an advocate entitled to practise, or an attorney`
  line `entitled to act, in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh or the High Court at Madras and was authorised to`
  line `appear or to act in any proceedings transferred under section 18 or section 19 shall have the right to`
  line `appear, or to act, as the case may be, in the High Court to which the proceedings have been transferred, in`
  line `relation to those proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39093)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39093&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 18 and 19,—`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings shall be deemed to be pending in the High Court of Andhra Pradesh or the High`
  line `Court at Madras until that Court has disposed of all issues between the parties, including any issue`
  line `with respect to the taxation of the costs of the proceedings and shall include appeals, applications for`
  line `leave to appeal to the Supreme Court, applications for review, petitions for revision and petitions for`
  line writs;
  line
  line `(b) references to the High Court of Andhra Pradesh or the High Court at Madras shall be`
  line `construed as including references to a Judge or division court thereof, and references to an order`
  line `made by a court or a Judge shall be construed as including references to a sentence, judgment or`
  line `decree passed or made by that Court or Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39127)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in transferred territories under existing appropriation Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39127&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or Madras before that day for the appropriation of any moneys out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of the State to meet any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1959-60 shall have`
  line `effect also in relation to the territories transferred to that State by the provisions of Part II and it shall be`
  line `lawful for the State Government to spend any amount in those territories out of the amount authorised by`
  line `such Act to be expended for any service in that State.`
  line
  line `(2) The Governor of Andhra Pradesh or of Madras may, after the appointed day, authorise such`
  line `expenditure from the Consolidated Fund of the State as he deems necessary for any purpose or service in`
  line `the territories transferred to that State for a period of not more than three months beginning with the`
  line `appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39095)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Reports relating to the accounts of Andhra Pradesh and Madras.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39095&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The reports of the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India referred to in clause (2) of article 151 of the Constitution`
  line `relating to the accounts of the State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras in respect of any period prior to the`
  line `appointed day shall be submitted to the Governor of each of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Madras`
  line `who shall cause them to be laid before the Legislature of the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39096)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Distribution of revenues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39096&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Section 3 of the Union Duties of Excise (Distribution)`
  line `Act, 1957 (55 of 1957), sections 3 and 5 of the Estate Duty and Tax on Railway Passenger Fares`
  line `(Distribution) Act, 1957 (57 of 1957), section 4 of and the Second Schedule to the Additional Duties of`
  line `Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957) and paragraphs 3 and 5 of the Constitution`
  line `(Distribution of Revenues) No. 2 Order, 1957, shall, as from the appointed day, have effect subject to`
  line `such modifications as the President may, by order published in the Official Gazette, specify having regard`
  line `to the transfer of territories effected by the provisions of Part II of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39097)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Land and goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39097&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Part, all land and all stores, articles`
  line `and other goods, including cash balances in all treasuries in the territories specified in the First Schedule`
  line `or the Second Schedule shall, as from the appointed day, pass to the State to which the territories are`
  line transferred.
  line
  line `(2) In this section, the expression "land" includes immovable property of every kind and any rights in`
  line `or over such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39098)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Arrears of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39098&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The right of Andhra Pradesh or Madras to recover arrears of any tax or duty`
  line `on property situate in the transferred territories, including land revenue, or to recover arrears of any other`
  line `tax or duty in any case where the place of assessment of that tax or duty is in the transferred territories`
  line `shall belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39099)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Right to recover loans and advances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39099&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The right to recover any loans or advances made before`
  line `the appointed day by Andhra Pradesh or Madras to any local body, society, agriculturist or other person in`
  line `the transferred territories shall belong to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39100)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Refund of taxes collected in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39100&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Andhra Pradesh or Madras to refund any`
  line `tax or duty on property situate in the transferred territories, including land revenue, collected in excess`
  line `shall be the liability of the State to which the territories are transferred, and the liability of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh or Madras to refund any other tax or duty collected in excess in any case where the place of`
  line `assessment of that tax or duty is in the transferred territories shall also be the liability of the State to`
  line `which those territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (39101)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Deposits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39101&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Andhra Pradesh or Madras in respect of any civil deposit or local fund`
  line `deposit made in the transferred territories shall, as from the appointed day, be the liability of the State to`
  line `which the territories are transferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (39102)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Provident Funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39102&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Andhra Pradesh or Madras in respect of the provident fund`
  line `account of a Government servant in service on the appointed day shall, as from that day, be the liability of`
  line `the State to which the Government servant is permanently allotted.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (39103)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Pensions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39103&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The liability of Andhra Pradesh or Madras in respect of pensions shall be apportioned`
  line `between those States in such manner as may be agreed upon between them or, in default of such`
  line `agreement, in such manner as the President may, by notified order, specify having regard to the transfer`
  line `of territories effected by this Act and the principles underlying the provisions of the Fifth Schedule to the`
  line `States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (39104)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Contracts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39104&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, before the appointed day, the State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras has`
  line `made any contract in the exercise of its executive power for any purposes of the State, that contract shall`
  line `be deemed to have been made in the exercise of the executive power,—`
  line
  line `(a) if such purposes are, as from that day, purposes relatable exclusively to the transferred`
  line `territories, of the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, of the State which made the contract;`
  line
  line `and all rights and liabilities which have accrued, or may accrue, under any such contract shall, to the`
  line `extent to which they are rights or liabilities of the State which made the contract, be rights or liabilities of`
  line `the State specified in clause (a) or clause (b) above.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, there shall be deemed to be included in the liabilities which have`
  line `accrued or may accrue under any contract—`
  line
  line `(a) any liability to satisfy an order or award made by any court or other tribunal in proceedings`
  line `relating to the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) any liability in respect of expenses incurred in or in connection with any such proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) This section shall have effect subject to the other provisions of this Part relating to the`
  line `apportionment of liabilities in respect of loans, guarantees and other financial obligations; and bank`
  line `balances and securities shall, notwithstanding that they partake of the nature of contractual rights, be dealt`
  line `with under those provisions.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (39105)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Liability in respect of actionable wrong.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39105&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras is subject to any liability in respect of an actionable wrong, other than`
  line `breach of contract, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the cause of action arose wholly within the transferred territories, be a liability of the State`
  line `to which they are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (39106)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Liability as guarantor of co-operative societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39106&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, the State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras is liable as guarantor in respect of any liability of a registered`
  line `co-operative society, that liability shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) if the area of the society's operations is limited to the transferred territories, be a liability of`
  line `the State to which the territories are transferred; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, continue to be a liability of the State which, immediately before that day,`
  line `was subject to such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (39107)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Items in suspense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39107&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If any item in suspense is ultimately found to affect an asset or liability of`
  line `the nature referred to in any of the foregoing provisions of this Part, it shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (39108)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of Central Government to order allocation or adjustment in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39108&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line Where
  line `either Andhra Pradesh or Madras becomes entitled to any property or obtains any benefits or becomes`
  line `subject to any liability, and the Central Government, on a reference made within a period of three years`
  line `from the appointed day by either of the States, is of opinion that it is just and equitable that that property`
  line `or those benefits should be transferred to, or shared with, the other State or that a contribution towards`
  line `that liability should be made by the other State, the said property or benefits shall be allocated in such`
  line `manner between the two States, or the other State shall make to the State subject to the liability such`
  line `contribution in respect thereof, as the Central Government may, after consultation with the two State`
  line `Governments, by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (39109)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Certain expenditure to be charged on the Consolidated Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39109&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `All sums payable by either`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or Madras to the other State by virtue of the provisions of this Part shall be charged on`
  line `the Consolidated Fund of the State by which such sums are payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (39110)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Provision as to certain financial Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39110&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, the Financial`
  line `Corporation constituted under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951 (63 of 1951), for the State of`
  line `Andhra Pradesh shall be deemed to have been constituted for that State with its area as altered by the`
  line `provisions of Part II of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) As from the appointed day, the Madras Industrial Investment Corporation constituted for the State`
  line `of Madras shall be deemed to have been constituted for that State with its area as altered by the provisions`
  line `of Part II of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (39111)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Amendment of Act 6 of 1942.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39111&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `In the Multi-Unit Co-operative Societies Act, 1942, in`
  line `section 5A, in sub-section (1), for the words and figures "any co-operative society which, immediately`
  line `before the 1st day of November, 1956", the words "or any other enactment relating to reorganisation of`
  line `States, any co-operative society which, immediately before the day on which the reorganisation takes`
  line `place" shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (39112)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Provisions as to State Electricity Boards and apportionment of their assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39112&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the appointed day, the State Electricity Boards constituted under the Electricity`
  line `(Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948), for the States of Andhra Pradesh and Madras shall be deemed to have`
  line `been constituted for those States with their areas as altered by the provisions of Part II of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The undertakings and assets of a State Electricity Board referred to in sub-section (1), situated in`
  line `the territories specified in the First Schedule or, as the case may be, the Second Schedule shall, as from`
  line `the appointed day, pass to the State to which the territories are transferred.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the assets and liabilities of the State Electricity`
  line `Boards referred to in sub-section (1) shall be apportioned between them in such manner as may be agreed`
  line `upon between the Governments of Andhra Pradesh and Madras within one year from the appointed day,`
  line `or in default of such agreement, as the Central Government may by order determine.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the arrangement which, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, was in force in regard to the generation or supply of electric power for the`
  line `territories specified in the First Schedule or the Second Schedule shall continue to be in force after the`
  line `appointed day on such terms and conditions and for such period as may be agreed upon between the`
  line `Governments of Andhra Pradesh and Madras, or, in default of such agreement, as the Central`
  line `Government may by order direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (39113)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Special provisions with regard to Araniar Project.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39113&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, all rights and liabilities of the State of Madras in relation to the Araniar Project or the`
  line `administration thereof shall, on the appointed day, be the rights and liabilities of the States of Andhra`
  line `Pradesh and Madras, subject to such adjustments as may be made by agreement entered into by the said`
  line `States or, if no such agreement is entered into within a period of one year from the appointed day, as the`
  line `Central Government may by order determine having regard to the purposes of the Project, and any such`
  line `order may provide for the management of the Project jointly by the said States or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the order so made by the Central Government may be varied by any subsequent`
  line `agreement entered into by the States of Andhra Pradesh and Madras.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement or order referred to in sub-section (1) shall provide also for the rights and liabilities`
  line `of the States of Andhra Pradesh and Madras in relation to any extension or further development of the`
  line `Project after the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(3) The rights and liabilities referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall include—`
  line
  line `(a) the rights to receive and to utilise water which may be available for distribution as a result of`
  line `the Project; and`
  line
  line `(b) the rights and liabilities in respect of the administration of the Project and the construction,`
  line `maintenance and operation thereof,`
  line
  line `but shall not include the rights and liabilities under any contract entered into before the appointed day by`
  line `the Government of Madras.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, from time to time, give such directions as may appear to it`
  line `necessary generally in regard to any of the matters specified in the foregoing provisions of this section`
  line `and, in particular, for the completion of the Project and its operation and maintenance thereafter:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be issued or have effect after an agreement has been entered into`
  line `by the States of Andhra Pradesh and Madras under sub-section (1) or after an order has been made by the`
  line `Central Government under that sub-section, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (39114)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Temporary provisions as to the continuance of certain existing road transport permits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39114&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 63 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), a permit`
  line `granted by the State Transport Authority of Andhra Pradesh or Madras or by any Regional Transport`
  line `Authority in such State shall, if such permit was immediately before the appointed day valid and effective`
  line `in any area within the transferred territories, be deemed to continue to be valid and effective in that area`
  line `after that day subject to the provisions of that Act as for the time being in force in that area; and it shall`
  line `not be necessary for any such permit to be countersigned by the State Transport Authority or any`
  line `Regional Transport Authority in the State to which the territories are transferred for the purpose of`
  line `validating it for use in such area:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after consultation with the State Government, add to,`
  line `amend or vary the conditions attached to the permit by the authority by which the permit was granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (39115)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Provisions relating to services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39115&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who, immediately before the appointed day,`
  line `is serving in connection with the affairs of Andhra Pradesh or Madras shall, as from that day, continue so`
  line `to serve, unless he is required by general or special order of the Central Government to serve`
  line `provisionally in connection with the affairs of the other State.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the appointed day, the Central Government shall, by general or special`
  line `order, determine the State to which every person provisionally allotted to Andhra Pradesh or Madras shall`
  line `be finally allotted for service and the date from which such allotment shall take effect or be deemed to`
  line `have taken effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person who is finally allotted under the provisions of sub-section (2) to Andhra Pradesh or`
  line `Madras shall, if he is not already serving therein, be made available for serving in that State from such`
  line `date as may be agreed upon between the two State Governments or in default of such agreement, as may`
  line `be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect, after the appointed day, the operation of the`
  line `provisions of Chapter I of Part XIV of the Constitution in relation to the determination of the conditions`
  line `of service of persons serving in connection with the affairs of Andhra Pradesh or Madras:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conditions of service applicable immediately before the appointed day to the case of`
  line `any person provisionally or finally allotted to Andhra Pradesh or Madras under this section shall not be`
  line `varied to his disadvantage except with the previous approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may at any time before or after the appointed day give such directions to`
  line `either State Government as may appear to it to be necessary for the purpose of giving effect to the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this section and the State Government shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (39116)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Provisions as to the continuance of officers in the same posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39116&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every person who,`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, is holding or discharging the duties of any post or office in`
  line `connection with the affairs of Andhra Pradesh or Madras in any area which on that day falls within the`
  line `other State shall continue to hold the same post or office in the State in which such area is included on`
  line `that day and shall be deemed as from that day to have been duly appointed to that post or office by the`
  line `Government of, or other appropriate authority in, such State:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent the competent authority, after the`
  line `appointed day, from passing in relation to such person any order affecting his continuance in such post or`
  line office.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (39117)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Territorial extent of laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39117&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 3 shall not be deemed to have effected any`
  line `change in the territories to which any law in force immediately before the appointed day extends or`
  line `applies, and territorial references in any such law to Andhra Pradesh or Madras shall, until otherwise`
  line `provided by a competent legislature or other competent authority, be construed as meaning the territories`
  line `within that State immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (39118)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to adapt laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39118&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of facilitating the application of any law in relation to`
  line `Andhra Pradesh or Madras, the appropriate Government may, before the expiration of one year from the`
  line `appointed day, by order make such adaptations and modifications of the law, whether by way of repeal or`
  line `amendment, as may be necessary or expedient, and thereupon every such law shall have effect subject to`
  line `the adaptations and modifications so made until altered, repealed or amended by a competent authority or`
  line `competent legislature.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section, the expression "appropriate Government" means, as respects any law`
  line `relating to a matter enumerated in the Union List, the Central Government, and as respects any other law,`
  line `the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (39119)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to construe laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39119&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that no provision or insufficient provision has been`
  line `made for the adaptation of a law made before the appointed day, any court, tribunal or authority, required`
  line `or empowered to enforce such law may, for the purpose of facilitating its application in relation to Andhra`
  line `Pradesh or Madras, construe the law in such manner, without affecting the substance, as may be necessary`
  line `or proper in regard to the matter before the court, tribunal or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (39120)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Power to name authorities, etc., for exercising statutory functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39120&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `The Government of the`
  line `State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras, as respects any territory transferred to that State by the provisions of`
  line `Part II, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify the authority, officer or person who, as from`
  line `the appointed day, shall be competent to exercise such functions exercisable under any law in force on`
  line `that day as may be mentioned in that notification, and such law shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (39121)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Legal proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39121&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where, immediately before the appointed day, the State of Andhra Pradesh`
  line `or Madras is a party to any legal proceedings with respect to any property, rights or liabilities transferred`
  line `to the other State under this Act, the other State shall be deemed to be substituted for the State from which`
  line `such property, rights or liabilities are transferred as a party to those proceedings, or added as a party`
  line `thereto, as the case may be, and the proceedings may continue accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (39122)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Transfer of pending proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39122&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending immediately before the`
  line `appointed day before a court (other than a High Court), tribunal, authority or officer in any area which on`
  line `that day falls within the State of Andhra Pradesh or Madras shall, if it is a proceeding relatable`
  line `exclusively to any part of the territories which as from that day are the territories of the other State, stand`
  line `transferred to the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer in the other State.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding should stand transferred under sub-section (1),`
  line `it shall be referred to the High Court having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which the court, tribunal,`
  line `authority or officer before which, or before whom, such proceeding is pending on the appointed day, is`
  line `functioning and the decision of that High Court shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "proceeding" includes any suit, case or appeal; and`
  line
  line `(b) "corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer" in a State means—`
  line
  line `(i) the court, tribunal, authority or officer in which, or before whom, the proceeding would`
  line `have lain if the proceeding had been instituted after the appointed day, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of doubt, such court, tribunal, authority or officer in that State as may be`
  line `determined after the appointed day by the Government of that State, or before the appointed day`
  line `by the Government of the other State, to be the corresponding court, tribunal, authority or officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (39123)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Right of pleaders to practise in certain courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39123&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, immediately before the`
  line `appointed day, is enrolled as a pleader entitled to practise in any subordinate courts in the transferred`
  line `territories shall, for a period of six months from that day, continue to be entitled to practise in those`
  line `courts, notwithstanding that the whole or any part of the territories within the jurisdiction of those courts`
  line `has been transferred to another State.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (39124)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Effect of provisions inconsistent with other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39124&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (39125)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39125&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the President may by order do anything not inconsistent with such provisions which appears to him`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (39126)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383&sectionId=39126&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00024_195956_1517807321383
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to give effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or ^1`
  line `[in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "in two successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the session in`
  line `which it is so laid or the session immediately following" (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
